  "text": "It does not appear therefore that promotion of the PI3K pathway by inhibition of PTEN using bpV(HOpic) is a candidate treatment for the robust generation of numbers of good-quality mature IVG human oocytes. Pharmacological manipulation of the PI3K pathway to promote follicle development has been successfully achieved in mice via promotion of other components of PI3K, e.g. by using 740Y-P [CITATION_1] , and it remains to be seen whether this molecule can be used to promote follicle activation and maintain morphologically normal growth in human ovarian follicles.",
